parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clock spring can cause the airbag warning light to illuminate, disabling the driver's side airbag, horn, and cruise control, which can increase the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The airbag warning light is illuminated
the cruise control does not work
the airbag light comes on intermittently
the horn and cruise control malfunction
the airbag may not deploy in an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Power steering failure can cause the steering wheel to become difficult to turn, making it hard to control the vehicle, especially at low speeds, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: Steering wheel becomes hard to turn
making a loud noise or whining sound
and difficulty turning left or right.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the steering rack and pinion can cause the steering wheel to become difficult to turn, making it hard to control the vehicle, especially at low speeds, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: Steering wheel becomes hard to turn
making a loud noise or clunking sound
and difficulty turning left or right.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the clockspring can cause the horn to malfunction, and the airbag system to deploy improperly, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
Failure of the transmission and hydraulic system can cause the vehicle to lose power, making it difficult to control, which can lead to accidents.
Malfunction of the electrical system can cause various systems to fail, such as the power windows, locks, and instrument panel, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
Body and paint issues can cause water leakage, rust, and corrosion, which can lead to structural damage and accidents.
The failure of the front sway bar link can cause the vehicle to vibrate or wander while driving, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: Rattling noise from the front end
wandering or pulling to one side
loose or disconnected sway bar link.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the strut and strut mount can cause the strut to break or fall off, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
The failure of the clock spring can cause the airbag light to come on and stay on, leading to potential airbag deployment issues.
symptoms: Airbag light comes on and stays on

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear axle and wheel can cause the vehicle to vibrate or lose control, leading to potential accidents.
The failure of the steering and suspension can cause the vehicle to vibrate or wander while driving, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
